UID:6me1fd3vjat7pkupt1llr0ukgo@google.com
CREATED:20250324T185612Z
DESCRIPTION:<span>Dear Friends of Bloominglabs\,</span><span>Makevention 20
 25 is scheduled for<span> </span></span><b>Sat.\, Sept. 27\, from 10 AM to 
 4 PM</b><span>\, at the Switchyard Park Pavilion. As always\, it is free to
  attend\, and family friendly.</span><span>However\, to make Makevention ha
 ppen this year\, the organizing committee is requesting a few more hands to
  assist with the process of putting on the event. We currently have<span> <
 /span></span><b>five</b><span><span> </span>committee members on the offici
 al roster and are seeking<span> </span></span><b>three</b><span><span> </sp
 an>more for a total of<span> </span></span><b>eight</b><span>.</span><span>
 You need not be a member of Bloominglabs to contribute to Makevention - sev
 eral of our past committee members\, including Laura Hohman and Jeannette L
 ehr (Chief Organizer for 2023 and 2024)\, have been friends of the space\, 
 generously dedicating their time and abilities to foster the local DIY/Make
 r community.</span><span>The next committee meeting is<span> </span></span>
 <b>Tuesday\, April 1\, 6PM-7PM</b><span>\, at Bloominglabs. At that time\, 
 we will assess the viability of the committee for this year\, assign tasks 
 for the current Makevention season\, and set the schedule for future meetin
 gs.</span><span>Please let me know if you have interest in organizing and I
  can get you connected.</span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250324T185612Z
LOCATION:Bloominglabs\, 1840 S Walnut St Suite #200\, Bloomington\, IN 4740
 1\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Makevention Planninng Meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
