BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20191110T180000Z
DTEND:20191110T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020721Z
UID:79ilut19isgpu36bmtv70bpbfs@google.com
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20190913T045614Z
DESCRIPTION:Come join us for a "Giving of Thanks" workshop in honor of one 
 of Bloominglabs' early champions\, Staci Radford-Vincent. During Bloomingla
 bs' early years\, we greatly benefited from our partnership with Wonderlab\
 , and that relationship was largely fostered by Staci. Her enthusiasm and c
 reativity inspired a lot of our first events. She was always willing to do 
 crazy workshops at Wonderlab and make fun things in sustainable ways.<br><b
 r>To thank Staci for her role in our early success\, we will hold a Scribbl
 eBots (<a href="https://www.exploratorium.edu/sites/default/files/pdfs/scri
 bbling_machines.pdf">https://www.exploratorium.edu/sites/default/files/pdfs
 /scribbling_machines.pdf</a>) workshop at Bloominglabs from 1pm to 4pm on S
 unday\, November 10th. Scribblebots are fun for adults\, so come make a bot
  and remember all the fun we had in those early Wonderlab workshops.&nbsp\;
  You don't need to be there the whole time\, but make sure you come early e
 nough to leave about a half an hour to make a robot.<br><br>This will be a 
 free workshop\, but donations will be collected and split at Staci's reques
 t between Wonderlab and Bloominglabs. We are family-friendly (kids under 12
  need a guardian) and refreshments will be provided.<br>See More<br><br>Thi
 s will be a free workshop\, but donations will be collected for Staci's fav
 orite charities - Wonderlab and Bloominglabs! We are family-friendly (kids 
 under 14 need a guardian) and refreshments will be provided.
LAST-MODIFIED:20191011T185819Z
LOCATION:Bloominglabs\, 1840 S Walnut St Suite #200\, Bloomington\, IN 4740
 1\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:"Giving of Thanks" Scribblebot Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
