BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260301T190000Z
DTEND:20260301T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020721Z
UID:1ndj5ohmf64d2iqensgjjn417c@google.com
CREATED:20260222T175728Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span>    <span><span><a href="https://bloominglabs.org/C
 AD_Workshop" target="_blank">https://bloominglabs.org/CAD_Workshop</a></spa
 n></span><br>                                                              
                                 <br><br><blockquote><p>Date: Sunday\, 1 Mar
 ch 2026</p><p>Time: 2PM to 5 PM</p><p>Location: <a href="https://bloomingla
 bs.org/Location" target="_blank">Bloominglabs</a> lounge</p><p>Suggested to
  bring a laptop with Windows\, Linux\, or MacOS\, and a mouse with a left b
 utton\, right button\, and scroll wheel.</p><p>Price: $20 for members of Bl
 oominglabs\, $40 for everyone else</p>    <p>Capacity: eight. Registration 
 upon payment.</p></blockquote><p>Some computers and mice will be available.
 Computer-Aided Design is an invaluable tool for planning many sorts of DIY 
 projects\, and unlocks the full capability of computer-controlled maker too
 ls like 3D printers and laser cutters. This workshop will teach the princip
 les used in most engineering CAD programs --  sketching\, constraining\, ex
 truding\, revolving\, mirroring\, patterning\, and assembling -- to design 
 functional 3D objects.</p><p>In this workshop\, we will use the fast and fr
 ee CAD program <a href="https://solvespace.com/index.pl" target="_blank">So
 lveSpace</a>. This program has a minimal approach to CAD\, making it faster
  to use and easier to learn than most others.</p><p>For people who are inte
 rested in using more powerful design tools\, skills learned in SolveSpace w
 ill transfer to most other engineering CAD programs\, like Autodesk Invento
 r and Dassault SolidWorks. Some that are available for zero cost to hobbyis
 ts are FreeCAD\, Autodesk Fusion 360\, PTC OnShape\, and Siemens Solid Edge
 .</p></span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260222T175728Z
LOCATION:Bloominglabs\, 1840 S Walnut St Suite #200\, Bloomington\, IN 4740
 1\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CAD Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
